'''Abadeh''' ({{lang-fa| آباده }}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''Ābādeh''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3051024}}</ref> is a city in  and the capital of [[Abadeh County]], in [[Fars Province]], [[Iran]]. Abadeh is situated at an elevation of {{convert|6200|ft|m|-1}} in a fertile plain on the high road between [[Isfahan (city)|Isfahan]] and [[Shiraz, Iran|Shiraz]], {{convert|140|mi|km}} from the former and {{convert|170|mi|km}} from the latter.<ref name="Chisholm">{{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Abadeh|volume=1|page=6}}</ref>  At the 2006 census, its population was 52,042, in 14,184 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|07}}</ref>  As of 2009, the population was estimated to be 59042.<ref>[http://www.amar.org.ir/DesktopModules/FTPManager/upload/upload2360/newjkh/newjkh/Q11.xls Iran Statics Organization]</ref>

It is the largest city in the [[Abadeh County|Abadeh]]-[[Eghlid]] district, which is famed for its carved wood-work, made of the wood of [[pear]] and [[box tree]]s.<ref name=Chisholm/> Sesame oil, castor oil, grain, and various fruits are also produced there. The area is famous for its [[Abadeh rug]]s.

==Landmarks and crafts==
Abadeh historical monuments include Emirate Kolah Farangi, Tymcheh Sarafyan and Khaje tomb, located in the Khoja mountains.
Abadeh crafts can be embroidered in cotton. The town also produces [[Abadeh rug]]s.

==Transportation==

'''[[Road 65 (Iran)|Expressway 65]]''' passes through Abadeh. This situation helps Abadeh to improve its capabilities compared to the neighboring city, [[Eqlid]]. [[Road 78 (Iran)|Road 78]] makes connections from Abadeh to [[Abarkuh]], [[Yazd]] [[Eqlid]] and [[Yasuj]]. It has a junction with [[Road 65 (Iran)|Abadeh Shiraz Expressway]] 24&nbsp;km south of the city. A road starts from Abadeh Ring Road to [[Soqad]] and [[Semirom]], [[Road 55 (Iran)|Road 55]]. 

The railroad from [[Isfahan]] to [[Shiraz]] passes Abadeh and there are train services at Abadeh Railway Station to Shiraz, Esfahan, Tehran and Mashad. Abadeh airport (OISA) was planned to be built in [[Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani]]'s presidential period.

==Sport==
Abadeh's main sport is [[Football (Soccer)|Football]], like the rest of the country. The main stadium is [[Takhti Stadium (Abadeh)|Takhti Stadium]] located in Mo'allem Square. The main team in Abadeh is [[Behineh Rahbar Abadeh F.C.]] which is currently playing in [[Iran Football's 3rd Division]] after finishing first in [[Fars Provincial League]] (FPL) last year. It played in [[Hazfi Cup 2010-11]] reaching the fourth round.

==Air Defense Base==
Iran announced in 2012 the construction of the largest air defense site in the southern Iranian city of Abadeh.

